# Caddy Configuration

- Ensure HTTPS/TLS behavior remains explicit and intentional.
- Preserve existing working routes unless replacement is validated.
- Validate each reverse proxy target host/port before deploying.
- Keep route matchers explicit and readable; avoid ambiguous catch-alls.
- Add or update health-check friendly endpoints when changing routing.
- Reference active config context when available: `@Caddyfile`.
